article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 65, Cleveland State 53
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Mike Schachtner scored a game-high 31 points as Wisconsin-Green Bay rallied from a 13-point halftime deficit to defeat Cleveland State 65-53 on Saturday night. J'Nathan Bullock scored 19 points to lead Cleveland State (6-11, 0-4 Horizon League), which scored just nine points in the second half after piling up 44 in the first 20 minutes. Cleveland State hit 7 of 11 3-pointers and shot 65.4 percent from the field in the first half to build a 44-31 halftime lead. Bullock was 6-of-6 from the field and had 15 points before the break. But the Vikings went scoreless for the first 11:21 and the Phoenix went on a 13-0 run to tie the game and a 21-9 run to end the game. The Vikings were just 3-of-20 (15 percent) from the floor in the second half, and Bullock was 1-of-7. Josh Lawrence added 13 points and 10 rebounds and Ryan Evanochko had eight points and six assists for the Phoenix (9-7, 1-2), who improved to 8-1 at home. Raheem Moss scored 12 points for Cleveland State.
